reviews.text: This was a nice place to stop off for lunch. We took home some rolls that were delicious and we stayed for lunch as well. The sandwich was alright but I think it just wasn't to my taste. The pasta salad was really good and also the tomato pesto soup. I'll definitely come back and try another order!

Under the weather and need soup so i was able to search this place. The soup and sandwich combo is a good deal. Soup is delicious and the sandwich is great! Tasty and not dry. It has mozarella and tomato makes it delicious. The cashier is friendly. I dd not wait too long for them to make my order. I will surely come back here

Sadly the sandwich I get every time I come has changed. The bread changes. Smaller and stale. Not like their old baguettes that were large and soft. Three slices of tomato and some mozzarella for $15. I paid $2 for prosciutto which they didn‚Äôt add which was a bummer. I did to go so I didn‚Äôt notice until I got to my office.  Will not return. Quality went WAY down

Honestly, it kind of bums me out seeing everyone flock to Uncommon Grounds next door for their puffy, average bagels while this place sits half-empty. So I‚Äôve started coming back here more often. The food's very good‚Äînothing fancy, but solid. Coffee is pretty good. My only real gripe is that sometimes the bread that comes with soup is too hard. Other than that, clean and friendly, no complaints.

Came because of the great reviews. The cashier was warm and attentive, and the rest of the staff were very friendly too. Unfortunately, the salmon bowl was bland with an overly sweet sauce, and the gluten-free dessert was also too sugary. Flies on the pastries didn‚Äôt help. A mixed experience‚ÄîI‚Äôd probably skip it next time, but it was worth a try.

Oh and how can I forget the turkey stuffing and cranberry sandwich!

detailedReviews.text: My husband loves the coffee beans here and their bagels are also incredible. The salad I got here about a year ago wasn‚Äôt that great. And the place is OK inside.

detailedReviews.author: Jay Jackson
detailedReviews.text: Everything was very good!

detailedReviews.author: Matthew S.
detailedReviews.text: I've ordered from here several times, most often the Black and Bleu sandwich which I find very flavorful! Excellent for dine-in or takeout.

detailedReviews.author: Sydney Madden
detailedReviews.text: Yummy food! Good service!

detailedReviews.author: Robyn Caldwell
detailedReviews.text: Bountiful at Frog Alley Catering brought more than just food‚Äîthey brought flavor, warmth, and rave reviews from our guests! Nick was so easy to work with‚Äîfriendly, flexible, and always responsive. We had very specific food preferences and they executed them perfectly. Everything was fresh, beautifully presented, and seriously delicious. I can‚Äôt count how many people told us, ‚ÄúThis is the BEST food I‚Äôve ever had at a wedding,‚Äù and we even caught some sneaking back for seconds! This isn‚Äôt your typical wedding catering‚Äîit‚Äôs elevated, thoughtful, and absolutely mouthwatering. Huge shoutout to Nick and the team for making our meal a highlight of the day.

detailedReviews.author: Peter S
detailedReviews.text: Tasty food and very friendly service. Plus 50% off pastries for the last hour before closing!

detailedReviews.author: Cole Yancey
detailedReviews.text: Got the Panzanella. The bread tasted stale, and was so hard that it was inedible. The contents of the sandwich were good so I just ate those. But the bread made sandwich really really bad. Better luck next time.

detailedReviews.author: Patrick Mason
detailedReviews.text: Like a better Panera, their soups, sandwiches and pastries are a must-try in the Albany area. Their cakes are also phenomenal.

detailedReviews.author: Guilderland Mom
detailedReviews.text: The salads are amazing. However, the portion size for takeout is almost half the size of dine in. Which makes it a horrible value. I would order here way more often if this was not the case.

detailedReviews.author: Anesa Brkanovic
detailedReviews.text: We ordered pickup. Very efficient and super tasty. Would highly recommend.

detailedReviews.author: Prof. John
detailedReviews.text: The staff are very friendly.  The pastry and bread is very good. The soups also when a kind i like. Have never done a set down meal but I am sure it is good . During the pandemic I would come over to support the business by buying what I could. Sometimes I was the only car in the parking lot. Always wore a mask and did the recommended protocol . BTW. The cheese rolls are so good. Glad when you get them with the soup.

detailedReviews.author: Ron Stafford
detailedReviews.text: Great sandwiches

detailedReviews.author: Liliya Warner
detailedReviews.text: Quality / portions of their food has gone down drastically - save yourself the trouble and go across the treat to Simone's. 2x the food for $5-8 less than Bountiful. I used to come here all the time, but now it's not really worth it.

detailedReviews.author: Net B.
detailedReviews.text: Under the weather and need soup so i was able to search this place. The soup and sandwich combo is a good deal. Soup is delicious and the sandwich is great! Tasty and not dry. It has mozarella and tomato makes it delicious. The cashier is friendly. I dd not wait too long for them to make my order. I will surely come back here

detailedReviews.author: Kelli Flack
detailedReviews.text: Food is always fresh and delicious.

detailedReviews.author: Sandra Neznamy
detailedReviews.text: We travel to Albany once/month and we always make sure to stop at Bountiful Bread for their delicious breads and more!

detailedReviews.author: Hatice Dayan
detailedReviews.text: It was a good choice for my breakfast experience. I tried it for the first time and I was really pleased. Everything was delicious.

detailedReviews.author: Shaw Rabadi
detailedReviews.text: The Italian Wedding Soup was awesome, the bacon cheddar quiche was amazing and the service was great by everyone!

detailedReviews.author: A W
detailedReviews.text: Great casual eating, sandwiches are amazing. Whenever I'm back in town, bountiful is one of the places that I always make my way to.

detailedReviews.author: Mark Davidson
detailedReviews.text: Fantastic lunch and breakfast spot

detailedReviews.author: Mark Boucher
detailedReviews.text: Food is great especially their tomato pesto soup.  But their staff are rude and don't like being asked questions while ordering.

detailedReviews.author: Elisa Williams
detailedReviews.text: My friend and I shared the apple/brie on bread with caramelized onions.  The bread was delicious.  We expected the apple to be room temp and it was cold, the brie and carmelized onions were ice cold.   The brie was the consistency of thick white flavorless liquid.  As though it came out of a squirt bottle.  We expected a delicious bubbly warm snack and what we received was not that.  Not that at all.

detailedReviews.author: Rev. Nadine Morsch (The Bootleg Bodhisattva)
detailedReviews.text: In addition to being a great spot for lunch and bakery treats, Bountiful Bread also donates their throw-away most evenings to different community food banks. They're excellent and they give back to the community. 10/10

detailedReviews.author: Leah Hallow
detailedReviews.text: Bountiful Bread is my treat whenever I‚Äôm in the area. The food is delicious and the service is excellent.

detailedReviews.author: Mallory W.B.
detailedReviews.text: Leaves a lot to be desired. You feel like it‚Äôs going to be so good‚Ä¶ but it‚Äôs overly priced nonsense. The place is dirty and the staff are more concerned with the latest gossip than helping customers. The entire dining room was filthy, food all over the tables and floor. Got two sandwhiches and 2 cookies‚Ä¶ was $50 and all of it was subpar. Basically flavorless eggs sandwhich with ONE eggs‚Ä¶. There was nothing to the sandwich. All the coffee was empty and a staff member had to be asked a few times by two different guests to please refill them. This is my 3rd time trying bountiful bread and needless to say, won‚Äôt be back. Not worth the money, the wait or the quality.

detailedReviews.author: Medic 117
detailedReviews.text: Chicken noodle soup with the pepper jack breadü§åüèæ

detailedReviews.author: Becky
detailedReviews.text: Great Service!  Awesome food!  My Fav the salads and soups üòã

detailedReviews.author: Brian Rashkow
detailedReviews.text:
While things may sometimes be a bit pricier here than some other bakeries, they absolutely make up for in quality of their bakes. All of their baked goods (cookies, cupcakes, muffins, etc.) are absolutely delicious and always stand out in my mind.

The best thing about bountiful bread is the service, particularly from the front of house/cashiers. Always greeted with a smile and a helpful word, the two women who I see regularly on the weekends are absolutely a highlight.

I would highly recommend this place to anyone who enjoys tasty baked goods, and a warm welcoming environment.

detailedReviews.author: Ricky Lark
detailedReviews.text: When we come to Albany to shop we always plan on having lunch (or breakfast or dinner) at Bountiful Bread. And we have for years! Wonderful choice of salads, sandwiches, and various soups. And delicious layer cakes, cup cakes, etc., too, for dessert. The Plaza around them has a lot of great shops. Worth the visit!

detailedReviews.author: Pujhitha Ramesh
detailedReviews.text: Has the best tomato pesto soup!!

detailedReviews.author: jeni bliss
detailedReviews.text: I got takeout.  The Vermont Turkey sandwich is always good.  It‚Äôs easy to order online and rewards are generous.

detailedReviews.author: S Silver
detailedReviews.text: We really enjoy everything especially Bountiful's soups and delicious muffins.

detailedReviews.author: jessica p
detailedReviews.text: Delicious food and a great, varied menu. Sweets are tasty as well. We‚Äôve ordered custom cakes from here and they‚Äôre darn good, too. Overall a great, clean vibe.

detailedReviews.author: Blanco Sauvignon
detailedReviews.text:
I ordered a delicious loaf of bread. But the best part of my visit was that, when I accidentally left my pocketbook on the handle of the bathroom, someone returned it to the cashier with everything in tact -- my wallet, cash, phone, and car keys! May God eternally bless the person who returned my bag because they truly blessed me. I have previously returned lost items, and I will definitely continue to do so, with passion!
P.s. Be careful hooking your items onto doors/cubbies at public places. Not everyone is as honest.

detailedReviews.author: Danielle Giglio
detailedReviews.text: Excellent!

detailedReviews.author: Kevin McKenna

detailedReviews.author: Meleah Lynn

detailedReviews.author: Linda Miller
detailedReviews.text: The caprese  sandwich was very good.  The baguette was fresh and not soggy.

detailedReviews.author: kailah correa
detailedReviews.text: I really just go there for one specific person who makes my salad amazing. Really does portion size and texture of salad to the Max. It‚Äôs the biggest reason I go there even for the price. I don‚Äôt mind splurging because of the customer service I receive when that specific person makes my salad.

detailedReviews.author: Dallas Garven
detailedReviews.text: They had the best breakfast sandwich ever. Definitely going to pay probably double what you would elsewhere for anything on their menu however it is fresh and absolutely delicious so well worth it

detailedReviews.author: betsy tanenhaus
detailedReviews.text: A regular spot for me. Excellent salads & soups. Homemade bread & baked goods. Always a 5 for me.

detailedReviews.author: Mike H
detailedReviews.text: Great food

detailedReviews.author: Elizabeth Duncan
detailedReviews.text: We have only picked up food to go but every meal has been outstanding!  Ordering on line is easy and the food is always ready when promised. All ingredients are so fresh and they have a wide variety of options. Highly recommend this place!

detailedReviews.author: Ljean Torres
detailedReviews.text: Thanks for the advice. The granola bar . The tea was the best I also loved the beautiful display of desserts

detailedReviews.author: Diane Dicl
detailedReviews.text: I had a delicious tuna  wrap from Bountiful Bread for dinner yesterday. The counter staff  greeted me and took my order. My takeout was ready within five minutes. The pasta salad was flavorful. Oil based with Italian seasoning. They have a large, diverse menu.

detailedReviews.author: Naomi Miller
detailedReviews.text: I went at the start of the day. Pleasant staff. I enjoyed how they interacted with each other. Felt very positive. Food was delicious, looked smelled and tasted so good! They have GF baked good, but all their delicious bread had gluten. I ate it anyway. No regrets!! I hot the South of the border sandwich, a massive cherry danish(because why not) that I did share and a homemade whoopie pie(not pictured). Those are my weakness. Say whoopie pie and I'm there!

detailedReviews.author: Laural Anne MacGregor
detailedReviews.text: Always great food and service!

detailedReviews.author: June Wang
detailedReviews.text: Haven't had my favorite "healthy omelette" for a long time. Besides the price hike, the takeout box leaked on the car seat, my hands ... after 10min driving to my office.  I barely managed to get to my office. Also didn't see jam for my toast.

detailedReviews.author: Vidu Kapoor
detailedReviews.text:
The order taker sets the tone, the girl taking our order was curt, uninterested. Now the food is great indeed but the start of our experience was spoiled by the 1 girl who seemed troubled by us ordering or asking any questions. If we want to eat out then we are hoping for a enjoyable experience. If you don't like people do t take a job where you have to deal with people. I will think twice before visiting this place. Disappointed.
On top she took our order wrong I stead of 1/2 & 1/2 she took down whole sandwich and 1/2 salad. How incompetent can some be !!!!

detailedReviews.author: Bram Freedman
detailedReviews.text: They were kind and friendly and made me feel at home! Can't  wait to explore more of their delicious food options !!

detailedReviews.author: Matthew Thornton
detailedReviews.text: Had a delightful dinner with 7 of my friends. As always it was good. Topped off dinner with a box of cupcakes and a box of cookies.

detailedReviews.author: Raymond Wolfe (Ray)
detailedReviews.text:
My wife and I went into this bakery and stood there while the person behind the counter talked on the phone for 10 minutes.
We weren't even acknowledged. She got off the phone, went to the back, and talked to the other employees. As we were deciding to leave, she came back to take our order.
The cinnamon coffee cake muffin we purchased was good,¬† but not worth the disrespect or the wait.

detailedReviews.author: Mary Sherman
detailedReviews.text: Cookies are awesome!  Great to bring into office for parties.  Especially the ones with chocolate fudge.  Thank you.

detailedReviews.author: Jordann Bastiani
detailedReviews.text: I love the ham and cheese sandwiche at bountiful bread I would highly recommend bountiful bread to anyone looking for good food

detailedReviews.author: Mark House
detailedReviews.text: Great for breakfast.  Excellent breads!

detailedReviews.author: Kamryn Baldwin
detailedReviews.text: Girl at the front with black hair was so sweet and helpful!

detailedReviews.author: Lauren Rauf
detailedReviews.text: Amazing service! Belle was very helpful!

detailedReviews.author: Jillian Greenslit
detailedReviews.text: Multiple gluten free bakery options. Kind, friendly service and very affordable for a quick breakfast treat. My kids have tried the danish and cinnamon rolls. Big hit! Belle was great!

detailedReviews.author: Caroline Salvadori
detailedReviews.text: Great place and great food! The girl with the black hair was so helpful and helped me pick out what to order. It was a 10/10! Definitely recommend.
